.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH tapectl-unit 1  "tapectl-unit " 
.SH NAME
tapectl\-unit \- Manage archival units
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtapectl unit\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage archival units
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output in JSON format
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be done without making changes
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fI<CONFIG>\fR
Path to config file
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-init(1)
Initialize a directory as an archival unit
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-init\-bulk(1)
Bulk\-initialize subdirectories as units
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-list(1)
List units
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-status(1)
Show unit status/details
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-tag(1)
Add/remove tags
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-rename(1)
Rename a unit
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-discover(1)
Scan watch_roots for .tapectl\-unit.toml dotfiles
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-check\-integrity(1)
Check file integrity against staged checksums
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-mark\-tape\-only(1)
Mark unit as tape\-only (local data can be deleted)
.TP
tapectl\-unit\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
